Here's a standard approach:

## 1. Define theme resource dictionaries

Create three XAML files (e.g., `Resources/Styles/LightTheme.xaml`, `DarkTheme.xaml`, `HighContrastTheme.xaml`):

```xml
<!-- LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="TextPrimary">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <!-- ... -->
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Use the same keys in every theme file with different values.

## 2. Create a theme service

```csharp
public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(string themeName)
    {
        var mergedDictionaries = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;

        // Remove existing theme dictionary (always at index 0, for example)
        var existing = mergedDictionaries.FirstOrDefault(d => d.Source?.ToString().Contains("Theme") == true);
        if (existing != null)
            mergedDictionaries.Remove(existing);

        var theme = themeName switch
        {
            "Dark" => new DarkTheme(),
            "HighContrast" => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _ => new LightTheme()
        };

        mergedDictionaries.Add(theme);

        // Persist choice
        Preferences.Set("AppTheme", themeName);
    }
}
```

## 3. Apply on startup

In `App.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "Light"));
}
```

## 4. Settings page picker

```xml
<Picker Title="Theme" SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged">
    <Picker.ItemsSource>
        <x:Array Type="{x:Type x:String}">
            <x:String>Light</x:String>
            <x:String>Dark</x:String>
            <x:String>HighContrast</x:String>
        </x:Array>
    </Picker.ItemsSource>
</Picker>
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    if (sender is Picker picker && picker.SelectedItem is string theme)
        ThemeService.ApplyTheme(theme);
}
```

## 5. Consume in XAML with `DynamicResource`

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource TextPrimary}" Text="Hello" />
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**
- Use `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) so changes propagate immediately.
- Keep identical keys across all three dictionaries.
- Persist the choice with `Preferences` so it survives app restarts.
